<br>
I think I was lotto captain of 99% of the raids Col and I led, plus some from other leaders. I've been experimenting with some new techniques too. Here's what I do:<br>
<br>
Write down the names and classes of every participant in the raid.<br>
Assign a number to each one, starting at 2.<br>
Make hotkeys of /ooc like:<br>
<br>
/ooc Temp 2, Col 3, Wendaar 4, Eowen 5<br>
/pause 20<br>
/ooc Simplie 6, Tikkeni 7....<br>
<br>
etc etc until you get everyone and their numbers announced to the raid. <br>
Let them know that number is valid for any raid-wide lotto.<br>
Write down clerics again on a separate piece of paper. <br>
<br>
Ok preparation is done, let the drops begin!<br>
<br>
1- If it's a rare gem (jacinth, diamond, blue diamond), it's a raid-wide lotto. <br>
2- if it's a cash item (sapphire, fire opal, jewellery pieces with no stats), lotto amongst the clerics.<br>
3- make sure you communicate with raid leader to follow lotto rules (NBG, etc)<br>
<br>
For every item that drops:<br>
<br>
1 - SHOUT at least 3 times what the item is, what the stats are and who can use. Remember to check if all races can use as well as classes.<br>
2 - SHOUT at least 3 times who gave you tells to be on the lotto. Check your main list to make sure they can use the item.<br>
3 - Assign a number to each person eligible for the lotto (i.e. Temp 2, Col 3, Eowen 4). SHOUT that at least 3 times<br>
4 - Do the /random 2 4 or whatever the number is<br>
5 - SHOUT the winner<br>
<br>
For every raid-wide lotto:<br>
<br>
1 - /random 2 to X (whatever the last assigned number is)<br>
2 - SHOUT the winner<br>
<br>
Make sure AFTER the lotto you:<br>
<br>
- write down the item lottoed beside the name of the winner so you don't allow them on another lotto later in the raid<br>
- make a mark beside the name of the cleric when they win cash items so you remove them from future cash lottoes until all clerics have something. Reset the list and include all clerics again.<br>
<br>
Other tips:<br>
<br>
Avoid being the lotto captain if:<br>
- you go LD a lot, AFK a lot or have bad lag<br>
- you are the puller, raid leader, main chanter or healer<br>
<br>
If you have a second computer near you, even better! Keep a list of zone drops near you!<br>
